10 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Strategic Military
Planning Commission; amending 74 O.S. 2021, Section
12 5401, which relates to creation of the Commission;
extending sunset date; updating statutory language;
13 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 5401, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 5401. A. There is hereby re-created the Oklahoma
20 Strategic Military Planning Commission.
21 B. The Oklahoma Strategic Military Planning Commission shall
22 consist of nine (9) members as follows:
23 1. Five persons to be appointed by the Governor, each of whom
24 shall represent, respectively, the interests of communities that
Req. No. 3603 Page 1

1 woul d be affected by realignment or closure of the following
2 military installations:
3 a. Altus Air Force Base,
4 b. Vance Air Force Base,
5 c. Fort Sill,
6 d. the Army Ammunition Plant located near McAlester, and
7 e. Tinker Air Force Base;
8 2. One person to be appointed by the Speaker of the House of
9 Representatives from the membership of the House and one person to
10 be appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the Senate from the
11 membership of the Senate. The members appointed pursuant to this
12 paragraph shall be ex officio and nonvoting members of the
13 Commission; and
14 3. The Secretary of Veterans Affairs, or successor member of
15 the Governor’s Executive Cabinet who has responsibility for Veterans
16 Affairs, and the Adjutant General of the Oklahoma Army and Air
17 National Guard. The members appointed pursuant to this paragraph
18 shall be ex officio and nonvoting members of the Commission.
19 C. The members of the Commission shall serve at the pleasure of
20 the appointing authority. The members of the Commission shall
21 select from among their membership a chair and vice-chair vice
22 chair. The chair and vice-chair vice chair shall serve for a period
23 of one (1) year and may succeed themselves in office.
24
Req. No. 3603 Page 2

1 D. The Commission shall be subject to the provisions of the
2 Oklahoma Open Meeting Act and the Oklahoma Open Records Act.
3 E. The Commission shall be authorized to meet at such times as
4 may be required in order to fulfill the duties and responsibilities
5 imposed upon it by law.
6 F. The provisions of this section shall cease to have the force
7 and effect of law and the Commission shall be dissolved by operation
8 of law on December 31, 2025 December 31, 2030.
9 G. The members of the Commission shall not be deemed to be
10 officers or to hold public office for purposes of Section 6 of Title
11 51 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
